Title: AUDEMARS PIGUET ROYAL OAK OFFSHORE ALINGHI TEAM CARBON + EXTRAS
Subtitle: Limited Edition of 1,300 pieces! Rare First Edition!
Description: Audemars Piguet Royal Oak Offshore Alinghi Team Carbon Special Limited Edition of 1,300 pieces dedicated to Alinghi and its crew, member of 32nd America's Cup. This watch is from the first and most collectable edition of this model with NO white outline around the Alinghi Logo located at the 3 o' clock position. Reference:26062FS.OO.A002CA.01 Mechanical automatic, exclusively produced AP Caliber 2326/2840 with circular-grained bridges hand-finished and decorated with Cotes de Geneve has a power reserve of about 40 hours. Functions include hours, minutes, chronograph with Fly-back function, regatta start function (central second's hand) and regatta countdown aperture. Titanium and Forged Carbon, 44 mm in diameter and 14.4 mm in height case, with a Forged Carbon octagonal bezel, Ceramic pushers and crown, anti-reflective sapphire crystal and PVD-coated Titanium case-back depicting a photo of Team Alinghi and bearing the inscription "Royal Oak Offshore Alinghi Team Limited Edition" is water resistant to 10 atm. Black-lacquered dial, with central zone with a grid pattern, applied printed Arabic numerals and skeleton hands with luminous coating and Alinghi logo. Black vulcanized rubber strap, fully integrated with the case middle, with an oversized Titanium PVD-coated tang bucke. This watch is pre-owned and comes complete with AP Warranty Booklet with dealer-stamped warranty, original AP rubber strap (used), two AP black “hornback” leather straps with red stitching (one used, one unworn), AP black “hornback” leather strap with black stitching and red edges (unworn) and special pins and screws to change the straps.
